Here are 15 factual question pairs based on the document:

1. Q: What is the purpose of a Personalausweis?
A: An identification document that serves as proof of identity.

2. Q: How can I obtain a new Personalausweis after losing or having it stolen?
A: By applying for a new one at the Hamburg Service or online.

3. Q: Can I apply for a Personalausweis online?
A: Yes, you can apply online and then pick up your document at the Hamburg Service.

4. Q: What is required to obtain a Personalausweis?
A: Biometric data (photo, fingerprints, signature) and personal identification information.

5. Q: How long does it take to process an application for a Personalausweis?
A: The processing time varies depending on the complexity of the case.

6. Q: Can I use my old Personalausweis until the new one is issued?
A: No, you must destroy your old Personalausweis once you receive the new one.

7. Q: What are the different types of Personalausweise available?
A: There are various types of identification documents, including a vorläufiger Personalausweis (provisional ID) and Neuer PA (new ID).

8. Q: How do I know if my biometric data is stored securely?
A: According to the document, all biometric data is deleted within 60 minutes or 12 hours of being accessed.

9. Q: Can I use a photo taken at a different location for my Personalausweis application?
A: No, you must take your photo at one of the Hamburg Service's Speed Capture Terminals or other authorized locations.

10. Q: What is the cost of having my biometric data processed at the Speed Capture Terminal?
A: The fee for this service is 6.00 EUR and will be added to the overall processing costs.

11. Q: Can I apply for a Fischereischein (fishing permit) or Führerschein (driver's license) at the Hamburg Service?
A: No, these documents require separate applications and biometric data that cannot be obtained through the Personalausweis application process.

12. Q: Are there any special requirements for applying for a Personalausweis as a person with disabilities?
A: Yes, the document provides information on services and accommodations available to individuals with disabilities who need to apply for an ID.

13. Q: Can I apply for a Personalausweis by phone or email?
A: No, you must apply in person at the Hamburg Service or online through their website.

14. Q: What is the purpose of the vorläufiger Personalausweis (provisional ID)?
A: A temporary identification document issued while your application is being processed.

15. Q: How can I contact the Hamburg Service for more information about applying for a Personalausweis?
A: You can find their contact information, including phone number and email address, at the bottom of the document.